E
globe~
A golden globe hovers in mid air.  It is surrounded by thousands of tiny
yellow pinpoints of light, only slightly larger than grains of sand, that
slowly orbit the globe.  A handful of the these pinpoints are white, instead
of the warmer hue of the rest, as if to make them stand out.  A single point
of light is bright green and contrasts sharply with the rest of the display.
You can also make out shapes in the otherwise chaotic distribution of these
orbiting lights, some which are eerily similar to some of the many
constallations visible in the night sky.  
~
